Key Match Events: Orlando Arcia hit his 14th homer of the year
Sean Murphy hit his eighth homer of the season
Arcia homered again in the sixth inning
The Braves hit at least three home runs in a game for the 26th time this season
Post-Match Reflections: Phillies manager Rob Thomson discussed the mislocation of pitches
Bryce Harper mentioned battling nagging wrist and elbow issues
Harper said the Braves are playing real good baseball right now
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ranger Suárez struck out the first five batters in his second start since missing a month with lower-back tightness
Suárez's ERA against the Phillies this season dropped to 1.06 over three starts and 17 innings
Phillies sent their condolences to the Gaudreau family
Phillies reliever José Alvarado returned to the team after being placed on the restricted list for a personal matter
Alec Bohm did not play due to a left hand injury
